10/08/2003
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Deputy Defence Minister Ilko Dimitrov announced that the 480-strong Bulgarian contingent is to leave for Iraq over three consecutive days, starting Monday (11 August).
The troops will fly to Kuwait and travel from there to their base camp in the town of Karbala.
A pilot group of 30 soldiers went to Karbala at the end of July to prepare the camp.
The Bulgarians are to serve under Polish command.
(BTA, Mediapool - 08/08/03)
